Crust: Place crumbs in bowl and drizzle with butter; using form, mix until combined. Transfer to 9-inch (23 cm) pie plate; press firmly into bottom and sides. Bake at 350 degrees F (180 degrees C) for 10 min. Cool. Filling: Blend eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter, vanilla, and salt in large bowl. Stir in pecans. Pour into prepared pie shell. Bake 35 to 40 min. or until set. Cool. Use serrated knife to cut.